# SpecForge Linear E2E configuration. Copy this file to `e2e/linear/.env` and
# fill it in. `e2e/linear/.env` is gitignored. Real shell env vars override
# anything set here.
#
# ⚠️  WARNING: this run CREATES and then DELETES real data (a Project, Issues, and
# Labels) in the target Linear workspace. Point it at a THROWAWAY / sandbox
# workspace only — NEVER a real project.

# --- Required ---
# A Linear Personal API key. Create one in Linear under
# Settings → Security & access → Personal API keys (sent as the raw token, no
# Bearer prefix). Treat it like a password — keep it in this gitignored file.
LINEAR_E2E_PAT=lin_api_replace-me

# The Linear team id (UUID) that will own the created issues. Find it in the
# team's settings URL, or via the API (`teams { nodes { id name } }`). Use a
# dedicated sandbox team so the create/delete churn is isolated.
LINEAR_E2E_TEAM_ID=replace-me

# --- Optional ---
# A Linear project id to group the created issues under. Usually unnecessary: the
# fixture's epic creates its own Project that the features/stories descend into.
#LINEAR_E2E_PROJECT_ID=
